Bank of Spain Backs Ibercaja, Unicaja Merger, Economista Reports

-- B y   S h a r o n   S m y t h
-- 
2011-03-08T06:51:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-08/bank-of-spain-backs-ibercaja-unicaja-merger-economista-reports.html
The Bank of  Spain  is backing a
merger among Spanish savings banks Unicaja, Ibercaja and Caja
Duero,  El Economista  reported, citing unidentified people with
knowledge of the situation.  The resulting entity would have assets of 125 billion euros
($175 billion), the newspaper said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Sharon Smyth in  Madrid  at 
 ssmyth2@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Blackman at 
 ablackman@bloomberg.net . 